<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Forked" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Forked,</orth> dividing into two: <cit><quote>f. heads,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 1, 24</bibl></cit> (== barbed arrow-heads). <cit><quote>o'er head and ears a f. one,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.186" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 186</bibl></cit> (== a horned cuckold); cf. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.2.178" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 2, 178</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.276" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 276</bibl>. <cit><quote>a serpent with f. tongue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.259" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 259</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he was like a f. radish,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.334" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 334</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a f. animal,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.113" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 113</bibl></cit> (two-legged). <cit><quote>a f. mountain,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 4.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 14</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 14</bibl>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>